{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17532977","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17532977"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:31:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:31:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14730"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14730","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14730"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.02,0.29,0.4,0.28]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7423"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115905"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7423","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7423"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14730"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97901"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18127"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36811"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38489"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38768"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40955"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40968"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41005"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41006"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45453"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45754"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49354"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115905","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115905"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic for routine follow-up three months after an inferior myocardial infarction. He has a medical history of hypertension and hypercholesterolaemia. His medications include aspirin, ticagrelor, metoprolol, ramipril, and atorvastatin. He has stopped smoking since his heart attack and walks for 30 minutes daily. On examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 65/min and blood pressure 142/88 mmHg. The remainder of his examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate target systolic blood pressure for this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["\u003C110 mmHg","\u003C150 mmHg","\u003C140 mmHg","\u003C130 mmHg","\u003C120 mmHg"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents for follow-up after a myocardial infarction with blood pressure above the recommended target.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAccording to the current Australian guidelines for hypertension management (2016), blood pressure targets should be individualised through shared decision-making between patient and clinician, taking into account the potential benefits and harms of treatment, and reviewed regularly. In general, a target blood pressure of \u0026lt;140/90 mmHg is recommended for patients with uncomplicated hypertension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever in patients at high of cardiovascular risk - such as those with previous myocardial infarction (as in this case) or stroke, diabetes with microalbuminuria, moderate to severe CKD or familial hypercholesterolaemia - more intensive systolic blood pressure targets (\u003Cstrong\u003E\u0026lt;120 mmHg) \u003C/strong\u003Emay be appropriate. This target is based on evidence showing reduced cardiovascular events and mortality with more intensive blood pressure control in high-risk patients. However, such targets require careful monitoring for treatment-related adverse effects, including hypotension, syncope, electrolyte disturbances, and acute kidney injury.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAchievement of target blood pressure typically requires a combination of lifestyle modifications (including dietary sodium restriction, regular exercise, and weight management if needed) and pharmacological therapy. Regular monitoring and medication adjustment are essential components of ongoing care.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Targeting a systolic blood pressure of \u003C120 mmHg in individuals with high cardiovascular risk may improve their cardiovascular outcomes.","Regular blood pressure monitoring and medication adjustment is essential for secondary prevention after myocardial infarction.","Lifestyle modifications including dietary sodium restriction and regular exercise are important adjuncts to pharmacological blood pressure control."],"references":["Gabb GM, Mangoni AA, Anderson CS, Cowley D, Dowden JS, Golledge J, Hankey GJ, Howes FS, Leckie L, Perkovic V, Schlaich M, Zwar NA, Medley TL, Arnolda L. Guideline for the diagnosis and management of hypertension in adults - 2016. Med J Aust. 2016 Jul 18;205(2):85-9. Available at: https://www.heartfoundation.org.au/for-professionals/hypertension","Atkins ER, Perkovic V. Blood pressure: at what level is treatment worthwhile?. Aust Prescr 2019;42:127-30. Available at: https://doi.org/10.18773/austprescr.2019.038"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97901"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14730"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97901","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97901"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-26T08:53:19+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-26T08:53:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7423"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115905"}